

Cardinality:

Types of cardinality:          
high cardinality:    EX:(more unique values:Email, phone number, customer_id)
medium cardinality;  EX:(Some repated+some unique, city, state, film title) 
low  Cardinality:    EX(Very few unique values	gender ,(M/F), status (Y/N), category_id

  There are 4Types of Relation ships in Cardinality
  

ONe- one

 Examples
Customer	   Cart
Customer 101	Cart 501
Customer 102	Cart 502
Example 2: Person ↔ Passport

One person has one passport.

One passport belongs to one person.

One-to-Many
Example 1: Customer → Address

One customer can save many addresses (Home, Office, Friend).

But each address belongs to only one customer.

 one-to many
 Examples:
Customer	Address
C101	Home Address
C101	Office Address
C101	Friend Address

Many-to-Many (M:N) — Examples
Example 1: Cart ↔ Products

One cart can have many products.

One product can be added to many customers’ carts.


Many-to many

Cart	Product
Cart 501	Product 10
Cart 501	Product 20
Cart 601	Product 10
Cart 601	Product 30

Bridge Table: to break many-many realtionships into one -many raltion
 
Joins:
Inner join: return matched columns on both table
left join: return all columns from left table and matched rows from right table
right join:return all columns from  Right table and matched rows from left table
full join: combine both table
cross join: Permutation and combination of each record

Inner Join:
SELECT c.first_name, p.amount
FROM customer c
INNER JOIN payment p
  ON c.customer_id = p.customer_id;
  
left join:
SELECT c.first_name, p.amount
FROM customer c
LEFT JOIN payment p
  ON c.customer_id = p.customer_id;  
  
  Right JOin:
  SELECT c.first_name, p.amount
FROM customer c
RIGHT JOIN payment p
  ON c.customer_id = p.customer_id;
  
  FULL Join:
  SELECT c.customer_id, p.amount
FROM customer c
LEFT JOIN payment p
  ON c.customer_id = p.customer_id
UNION
SELECT c.customer_id, p.amount
FROM customer c
RIGHT JOIN payment p
  ON c.customer_id = p.customer_id;
  
  
  Cross Join:
  SELECT f.title, c.name
FROM film f
CROSS JOIN category c;
  
  
  

